div.p:
In conclusion For you of his dear, and beloved Flock, this may be directive to you as well as consolatory;
would you have a Pastor after God's Heart? put your selves under the conduct, as much as in you is, of such a Pastor, as you apprehend will be intent, in all his Ministrations, upon this double end, to save himself, and them that hear him. And labour to be perfect, be of one mind, and live in Peace, so the God of 2 Cor. 13. 11. Love and Peace shall be with you. And remember him as one that hath had the Rule over you, and hath spoken to you the word of the Lord, and follow the Faith of such, considering the end of their Conversation; and that Jesus Christ is the same, yesterday, and to day, for ever. As you change Pastors you will not need to change Christs, so as to have one yesterday, another to day, and a third to morrow. Pastors under the Gospel, as well as Priests under the Law were many, because of death. But our B. Lord, because he continueth ever, hath an unchangeable Priesthood, Heb. 7. 24. Therefore do you never think of another Christ, as their doubt was, Matt. 11. 3. but cleave
to this your great Lord with purpose of Heart, till he give you at last, an abundant entrance into his everlasting Kingdom.
